
tint2 is a Freedesktop-compliant taskbar that aims to be lightweight and unintrusive.tint2 homepage tint2's code is based on tint task manager. Some of tint2's features include a system tray, a clock, and a battery monitor. Its lightweight design makes it suitable for use with window managers such as Openbox, and it is included as part of the default desktop on CrunchBang Linux.
tint2 ranks 9374 in the Debian Popularity contest.Popularity Contest Statistics

